President Barack Obama has proclaimed September 11, 2016, as National Grandparents Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the important role that grandparents play in families and communities. He acknowledges their wisdom, devotion, and the progress they have made to create a better world for their children and grandchildren. President Obama also recognizes the sacrifices that some grandparents have made, such as fighting for freedom or starting a new life in America. He emphasizes the responsibility of ensuring that grandparents can retire with security and dignity. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to honor their own grandparents and those in their community.